<doc id="40754" wikidata="Q4826579" url="?curid=40754" title="Automatic message exchange">
<text>Automatic message exchange (AME): In an adaptive high-frequency (HF) radio network, an automated process allowing the transfer of a message from message injection to addressee reception, without human intervention. Through the use of machine-addressable transport guidance information, &quot;i.e.,&quot; the message header, the message is automatically routed through an on-line direct connection through single or multiple transmission media.

