<doc id="40775" wikidata="Q4867028" url="?curid=40775" title="Basic exchange telecommunications radio service">
<text>In telecommunications, a basic exchange telecommunications radio service (BETRS) is a commercial service that can extend telephone service to rural areas by replacing the local loop with radio communications. In the BETRS, non-government ultra high frequency (UHF) and very high frequency (VHF) common carrier and the private radio service frequencies are shared.

