<doc id="40789" wikidata="Q4907585" url="?curid=40789" title="Bilateral synchronization">
<text>In telecommunications, bilateral synchronization (or bilateral control) is a synchronization control system between exchanges A and B in which the clock at telephone exchange A controls the data received at exchange B and the clock at exchange B controls the data received at exchange A. 

Bilateral synchronization is usually implemented by deriving the timing from the incoming bitstream.

Source: from Federal Standard 1037C in support of MIL-STD-188

== See also ==
