<doc id="40871" wikidata="Q5121606" url="?curid=40871" title="Circuit noise level">
<text>At any point in a transmission system, the ratio of the circuit noise at that point to an arbitrary level chosen as a reference. 

The circuit noise level is usually expressed in dBrn0, signifying the reading of a circuit noise meter, or in dBa0, signifying circuit noise meter reading adjusted to represent an interfering effect under specified conditions. </text><links>
