<doc id="40872" wikidata="Q5121614" url="?curid=40872" title="Circuit reliability">
<text>Circuit reliability (also time availability) (&quot;CiR&quot;) is the percentage of time an electronic circuit was available for use in a specified period of scheduled availability. Circuit reliability is given by where &quot;T&quot; o is the circuit total outage time, &quot;Ts&quot; is the circuit total scheduled time, and &quot;T&quot; a is the circuit total available time. formula_1 

In addition, circuit reliability is the expected lifespan of operation of a functioning system under nominal conditions.

