<doc id="40891" wikidata="Q863873" url="?curid=40891" title="Code word (communication)">
<text>In communication, a code word is an element of a standardized code or protocol. Each code word is assembled in accordance with the specific rules of the code and assigned a unique meaning. Code words are typically used for reasons of reliability, clarity, brevity, or secrecy.

