<doc id="40901" wikidata="Q16769588" url="?curid=40901" title="Comma-free code">
<text>A comma-free code is block code in which no concatenation of two code words contains a valid code word that overlaps both.

Comma-free codes are also known as &quot;self-synchronizing block codes&quot; because no synchronization is required to find the beginning of a code word.

