<doc id="40933" wikidata="Q5156428" url="?curid=40933" title="Complementary network service">
<text>In telecommunications, a complementary network service (CNS) is a means for an enhanced-service provider customer to connect to a network and to the enhanced service provider. 

Complementary network services usually consist of the customer local service, such as a business or residence, and several associated service features, such as a call-forwarding service.

