<doc id="40961" wikidata="Q5165874" url="?curid=40961" title="Control operation">
<text>In telecommunications, a control operation (control function) is an operation that affects the recording, processing, transmission, or interpretation of data. 

Examples of control operations include a font change, or a rewind; and transmitting an end-of-transmission (EOT) control character.

